        "media_with_content_CDceeb": {
          "type": "media_with_content",
          "settings": {
            "kicker": "",
            "heading": "<p>Most decaf in America is made with <br/>methylene chloride or ethyl acetate. <br/>solvents. If a bag of decaf has ever <br/>smelled like nail polish, that’s ethyl <br/>acetate residue.</p>",
            "body": "<p>Both are “below the legal limit” by FDA standards. We think “below  the legal limit” is the bare minimum, not the goal.<br/><br/>Heist is decaffeinated with only water. The caffeine dissolves out while the delicious flavor stays. <br/><br/>Jarrett tests every batch for mold, mycotoxins, and heavy metals. If a lot doesn’t pass, it doesn’t ship. The full. process is on our <a href=\"#\" title=\"#\">Process Page</a>. The receipts are too.</p>",
            "media_position": "left",
            "media_inline": true,
            "media_type": "video",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Frame_1410127384.jpg",
